      "ideas": [
        {
          "title": "Calendly's Quiet Pivot Signals Category Collapse",
          "idea": "**Concept:** Scheduling company reorienting toward \"relationship management\" **Pattern:** When adjacent categories (scheduling, CRM, email, AI assistants) all converge on \"relationship management,\" the boundaries dissolve. Every productivity tool becomes a CRM. **Question:** Does Zo win by racing to relationship management, or by remaining the integration layer while others fight for CRM positioning? --- *Note: These ideas are observation-level, not recommendation-level. No actions implied.*",
